comments:
Knowledge: More in depth understanding of mostly molecular biology (e.g. DNA, genetics, prokaryotic and eukaryotic replication translation and transcription, etc);

Skills: Reading primary literature and answering questions from primary data (most of the problem set and exam questions are based on primary research data, some of which are more recent publication and some are based on seminal works in the field);

Insight: Best ways to learn from ad prepare for higher level coursework that are more based on research, data interpretation, and less about regurgitation of facts (and even more based on primary research instead of hypothetical conceptual scenarios)
